Problem 7

Part A

Part D

layout(matrix(c(1,2), 2, 2, byrow = TRUE))

for (i in 3:length(Boston) - 1) {
  cat(colnames(Boston)[i])
  cat('\n===================')
  fit = lm(crim ~ poly(Boston[,i], degree=3, raw=TRUE), data=Boston)
  print(summary(fit))
  plot(Boston[,c(1, i)])
  abline(fit)
  predict(fit, data.frame(crim = 0:80))
}
